{"article_id":"JI0UP4rXGKB0dlgJ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"There has n't been a school strike in Chicago for 25 years .","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"But the current contract between Chicago teachers and the Chicago Public Schools expires at the end of next week ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"and tensions between the teachers union , the school district and Mayor Rahm Emanuel are ratcheting higher .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Chicago Teachers Union members outmaneuvered the mayor , school officials and anti-union education groups","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"by overwhelmingly approving a measure","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"that allows teachers to strike","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"if contract negotiations fall flat .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"About 90 percent of CTU 's membership","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"- nearly 24,000 workers -","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"voted this month","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"to support a strike","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"if one is called .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"The dispute has prompted comparisons to Wisconsin ,","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"where a firestorm over collective bargaining ultimately resulted in a recall election there earlier this month .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"CTU President Karen Lewis says","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"the strong vote in Chicago is an indication of the rocky relationship between the union and the school board .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"It also demonstrates `` the absolute abject lack of respect and scapegoating of teachers , paraprofessionals and clinicians throughout this country , ''","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"she says .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"`` That 's all","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"we hear , ''","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"Lewis says .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"`` [ That ] everything","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that 's wrong with the educational system","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"is our fault . ''","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"In the past year , Emanuel stripped teachers of a 4 percent pay raise ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"and his effort","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"to institute longer school days","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"while sidestepping the union contract","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"has infuriated union members .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"Emanuel also wants more privately run charter schools in the city ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"which the teachers union opposes .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"A change in state law also angered teachers .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"Aimed at preventing a strike ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"the new law set the threshold for a strike authorization vote at 75 percent","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"- and ruled","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"that those members","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"who do n't vote","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"would be considered `` no '' votes .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Michael Bochner , an art teacher at Cesar Chavez Elementary School , says","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"when teachers learned of the provision ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"they realized","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"the law was a huge effort","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"to blunt the union 's power .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"`` So here at Chavez , we had 100 percent participation on the first day","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"[ of voting ] ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"which is much more","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"than we 've had for any election ever before , ''","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Bochner says .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Emanuel denies","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"that his support for the change in the law backfired","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"- but he did acknowledge last week","depth":4},{"id":52,"text":"that the strong 90 percent vote is a `` huge number . ''","depth":4},{"id":53,"text":"School district and union negotiators are wrangling over wages , class size and other issues .","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"Even so , Emanuel offered a small olive branch last week","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"as he talked about the wide gap in the two sides ' proposals for teacher pay raises .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"`` They deserve it .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"They 've earned it","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"and appropriately have gotten it ,","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"and should get it in the future , ''","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Emanuel said .","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"`` What I want to make sure is our children also have a full day and full school year equal to their full potential ,","depth":4},{"id":62,"text":"which has not been done to date . ''","depth":4},{"id":63,"text":"Chicago Public Schools CEO Jean-Claude Brizard adds","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"that no one in the city is looking to mirror Wisconsin ,","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"which grabbed the country 's attention for months","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"after Gov . Scott Walker introduced contentious changes","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"curtailing the collective bargaining ability of most public-sector unions .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"`` No Wisconsin here","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"- and I do n't think","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"we need Wisconsin here , ''","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Brizard says .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"`` But ... I do n't want my kids being caught in the middle of all of this .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"I do n't want my families anxious about what 's going to be happening in September . ''","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"Robert Bruno , a labor professor at the University of Illinois , Chicago , says","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"while both the union and school board can draw lessons from the Wisconsin saga ,","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"Emanuel","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"- former chief of staff to President Obama -","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"may have another question","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"to consider .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"`` How exactly does it look to have a major collective-bargaining dispute","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"- a strike of public-sector workers -","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"in his home city , on the eve of a tight presidential election with battleground states all around Illinois ? ''","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Bruno asks .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"It may not come to that .","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"Both the union and the school board say","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"they 're looking for common ground","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"as the negotiations continue .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"And ,","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"says CTU 's Karen Lewis ,","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"that 90 percent strike authorization vote is making those negotiations just a little bit easier .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":183,"left":144,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":140,"right":143,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":105,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":94,"right":104,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":94,"left":0,"right":93,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":102,"right":103,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":97,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":3,"right":96,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":4,"right":95,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":99,"right":100,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":12,"right":